Such hurtful words!<br>
<br>
I've said this before, and I'll say it again.  My responsibility only lies in keeping Heaven and Earth alive and thriving, not other guilds.  What happens to other guilds is no obligated concern of mine.  My recruitment is open for certain classes because I need to replace people my guild lost.  Summer starts, people quit/sell, whatever, I need to replace my ranks.  Where do you think the players will come from?  Space?<br>
<br>
Whatever happens in other guilds that causes their members to become unhappy, or simply unsatisified, isn't my issue.  Any guild that thinks they can indefinitely maintain a combination of casual and hardcore players obviously hasn't learned from what happened to TWC.  That's not my problem, either.<br>
<br>
Would it make you feel better if I let HnE get crappy so other guilds would pass us and I could whine and cry alongside of you while my members left to join other guilds?  It's a game, and people have their goals.  I don't expect unfailing loyalty and eternal membership from the people in Heaven and Earth; I expect them to follow instructions, attend raids, and pay attention.  It baffles me that other guilds seem to expect more of their members.<br>
