Glad to see everyone is ok. What’s going on in Fam now is nothing new. No one wants Fam to be a stepping stone guild, but when you have such a large player base of casual gamers there is no two ways about it. How long will you be able to satisfy someone that wants to more foreword at a consistent pace? Kraz lasted a long time and so did many others who left, but in the end there are very few guilds that can keep people interested in the game and keep things new and fresh.<br>
<br>
One thing I’ve learned, that I will take with me to WoW, is to never join a guild that is based on friendship, family and an online chat room. I want gamers that log in to play a video game and leave real life out of it. I don’t need Mr.Cleric to be my friend. I have real life friends and family. I just need someone to have a good time in game with for the couple of hours per night I’m going to play it. Drama and politics in these kinds of games need to die. At least for me they do. I play to kill mobs and get loot. When I feel the need to talk to friends I call them up on the phone.<br>
